<subSubSection id="C311655C653AFFB0FCB14070EC79FE4F" pageId="4" pageNumber="31" type="biology_ecology">
<paragraph id="8BB436D7653AFFB0FCB14070EC79FE4F" blockId="4.[151,1437,152,564]" pageId="4" pageNumber="31">
<emphasis id="B97FEAC5653AFFB0FCB14070EEFBFE99" bold="true" box="[198,509,306,332]" pageId="4" pageNumber="31">Ecology and Phenology:</emphasis>
— 
<taxonomicName id="4C0B4D54653AFFB0FE6D4070EC55FE9E" authorityName="Melai &amp; Marchetti &amp; Bernardello &amp; Peruzzi" authorityYear="2012" box="[538,851,306,331]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Leucanthemum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="4" pageNumber="31" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="ligusticum">
<emphasis id="B97FEAC5653AFFB0FE6D4070EC55FE9E" box="[538,851,306,331]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="31">Leucanthemum ligusticum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
grows in open rocky places (
<quantity id="4CF39B32653AFFB0F8B04070EA62FE99" box="[1223,1380,306,332]" metricMagnitude="2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="6.3" metricValueMax="10.6" metricValueMin="2.0" pageId="4" pageNumber="31" unit="m" value="630.0" valueMax="1060.0" valueMin="200.0">200–1060 m</quantity>
), on siliceous substrates and deep-oceanic siliceous sedimentary rocks (&quot;diaspri&quot;). It is a hemicryptophyte, flowering from the beginning of May until the first half of July.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C311655C653AFFB0FCB140E4EE16FA0A" pageId="4" pageNumber="31" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="8BB436D7653AFFB0FCB140E4EED2FDE1" blockId="4.[151,1437,152,564]" pageId="4" pageNumber="31">
<emphasis id="B97FEAC5653AFFB0FCB140E4EE6FFE15" bold="true" box="[198,361,422,448]" pageId="4" pageNumber="31">Distribution:</emphasis>
— 
<taxonomicName id="4C0B4D54653AFFB0FDF140E5EDC4FE15" authorityName="Melai &amp; Marchetti &amp; Bernardello &amp; Peruzzi" authorityYear="2012" box="[390,706,423,448]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Leucanthemum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="4" pageNumber="31" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="ligusticum">
<emphasis id="B97FEAC5653AFFB0FDF140E5EDC4FE15" box="[390,706,423,448]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="31">Leucanthemum ligusticum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is currently known from few localities in eastern 
<collectingRegion id="49CFF835653AFFB0F93240E4EA9DFE15" box="[1349,1435,422,448]" country="Italy" name="Liguria" pageId="4" pageNumber="31">Liguria</collectingRegion>
(provinces of Genova and La Spezia; 
<figureCitation id="13302A52653AFFB0FE1F408FEDB4FE32" box="[616,690,461,487]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="4.[151,244,1242,1263]" captionTargetBox="[166,1423,609,1225]" captionTargetId="figure-467@4.[151,1436,609,1252]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 3. Leucanthemum ligusticum sp. nov. Known geographical distribution in eastern Liguria (northwestern Italy Italy)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5065882" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5065882/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="31">Fig. 3</figureCitation>
). Besides the three studied populations, the new species was observed near Bargone (Genova province), Mounts Roccagrande-Tregìn, 
<quantity id="4CF39B32653AFFB0F85740B6EBACFDDB" box="[1056,1194,500,526]" metricMagnitude="2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="6.25" metricValueMax="8.5" metricValueMin="4.0" pageId="4" pageNumber="31" unit="m" value="625.0" valueMax="850.0" valueMin="400.0">400–850 m</quantity>
and near the top of Mount Verruga, at 
<quantity id="4CF39B32653AFFB0FD034358EED6FDE1" box="[372,464,538,564]" metricMagnitude="3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.06" pageId="4" pageNumber="31" unit="m" value="1060.0">1060 m</quantity>
.
</paragraph>
<caption id="DF74665F653AFFB0FCE04598EA4BFB25" ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5065882" ID-Zenodo-Dep="5065882" box="[151,1357,1242,1264]" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5065882/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="31" startId="4.[151,244,1242,1263]" targetBox="[166,1423,609,1225]" targetPageId="4">
